archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.name: Tech Services Architecture Threat Chain
archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation:
This is the Tech Services Architecture Threat Chain. Itâ€™s important to understand the cause and effect of not doing architecture design as we see it every day.
It's common to misunderstand security architecture and assume it is only relating to hackers and threats relating to things like firewalls and security incidents. Security design is about protecting the business, and as such the cost of poor security architecture is reflected in the total cost of poor quality and controls should be impacting People, processes, information, governance, tools, technology, and the organization.
Print this. Stick it on the wall. next time you have an escalation, see if you can trace it back to a failure in architecture design. It's important to note, that there technically is not a start and end to this view. The threats and losses are impacting on each other and having a cyclic effect where things get worse over time. To make it easier to understand some of the threat events have been made large and bold, and act as a good starting point for reading this view.
